<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=9869799879561></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f9869799879561><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=7&mid=9869799879561>Halfing is the best race for a cleric.</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=7&mid=9869799879561#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=46955><span id=Sage>aeriform</span></a>, <span id=Sage>Sage</span><br><span id=notbold>66 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Wed, Apr 11th 5:06 AM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[3.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Currently you'll level as fast as every one else when you're grouped, but if you get power leveled or solo undead and such you'll level about 10% faster with a halfling.<br><br>Halflings are a mix between High Elves and Dwarves in that your strength and wisdom are mediocre but you have fantastic agility. in fact bumb your agility up to 100 to get a little bonus with the rest in wisdom and you'll be looking good. Strength doesn't matter too much because many classes (including yourself) get strength buffs and you wear small armour which will reduce your weight a bit. Plus hide and sneak (important because clerics don't get a regular invisibility spell) and an above average starting grounds.<br><br>The low charisma lowers the chance one or two new post level 50 spells will work. On the other hand low charisma will help with all of your fear spells, and there's a lot of them :OP<br><br>Plus the most important point is that you get furry feet :OP<br>&nbsp;<br><br>Hope this helps,<br><br>Aeriform,<br>Tunare & Torv. Worlds</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 >&nbsp;</td><td align=right valign=bottom>
	   <span style='font-weight: normal; font-size: 9px;'>[<a href=#top>Top</a>]</span></tr>
	   </form></table><ul>
<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=98821250579266></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f98821250579266><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=7&mid=98821250579266>RE: Halfing is the best race for a cleric.</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=7&mid=98821250579266#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=35078><span id= >Gestalt</span></a>, <span id= > </span><br><span id=notbold>115 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Wed, Apr 25th 11:28 AM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[2.80]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Hide and sneak are fine, so long as people understand that no class other than rogue can combine hide/sneak at same time.&nbsp;&nbsp;Many don't seem to understand that and it could confuse people that don't.<br><br>Also, low charisma has no effect on fear.  And neither does high charisma either.  Necros with horrible cha and enchanters with 200ish cha using the same fear spell and both same level, will both fear the same.  Sure, you could get a string of resists or short fears as either of them.  But that's chance.  Fear kiting with either is great, really only determining factor is level deifference, MR of mob, and what fear spell is being used (higher ones generally work better, or least they SHOULD, hehe).  So the cha of cleric means nothing for fearing...  What it will mean is he'll need a lot more cha boosting items or have someone cha buff him with a spell so he can buy his all important gems for hp buffs.<br><br>BTW, I have a DE cleric, and his cha sucks at 60 (i think).  Gotta get him buncha plus charisma items so he doesn't go into the poor house buying gems and spells in later levels.<br>&nbsp;<br>Gestalt<br>60 Grandmaster<br>ARo</td></tr>
