<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=98678988376444></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f98678988376444><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=7&mid=98678988376444>RE: looking for advice</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=7&mid=98678988376444#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=340><span id=Scholar>Chakfor</span></a>, <span id=Scholar>Scholar</span><br><span id=notbold>33 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Mon, Apr 9th 12:18 AM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[3.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Your best bet for earrings are gold/jasper. They're cheap and since most enchanters are working jewelry skills up like mad if you find a jeweler starting out he might make them for cost. The +3 wis in each ear will outweigh 10 mana. <br><br>If you're hunting Great Divide you might hit the next zone over and fight Ulthorks in Eastern Wastes for a while. They drop some 8ac +3wis -3dex sleeves that are nice for clerics. The plat arms are another bet, a bit more expensive (ulthorks free if you loot it) and they have no AC but they're +3 str and you don't take a hit on Dex.<br><br>Wrist slots are a bit tougher, I used a bracer of Erolisi(sp?) on one wrist and a banded bracer on the other. Remember, I wasn't a twink :) The bracer of Erolisi is +5 str and that's actually a fairly important stat for clerics I've found. If you wish you can buy two Chipped bone bracers or two polished bone bracers. Either are nice for nearly any level. I went with a RMB and a CBB when I could afford new equipment. You can camp either of these drops btw, no use in buying if you don't have to. <br><br>The mammoth hide cloak is almost a must. I stayed in Perma for 16 long and very boring hours at level 35 camping it. The alchemist seems to be a buggy spawn as well. It's supposedly a 20 min spawn timer. In the times I was there I got a PH about 12 times and the Alchemist twice. That's in 16 hours and none of the spawns were regularly timed. Either it skips or isn't really *fixed*, and since I've not heard of a spawn that didn't have a time I supposed it skips.<br><br>If you're high enough level to hunt at the giant fort and are a casting class I'd highly suggest it. Just offer to buy the weapons dropped by the giants as your group is disbanding for the day and before you log off ooc to the zone you're running an ATM service. I've gotten a TP to BB and limped to Kaladim with a 192/110 weight factor before. I made 400 plat that night and about 100 of it was off drops I had won. Then just gate back :) This is even better if you're a druid or wizard.<br>&nbsp;<br>"You want proof of Brell's power? The proof is in the bottle, the higher the proof the better!"</td></tr>
