	   <tr><td colspan=2>You are correct in assuming that the armors are nigh-impossible to acquire. You'll need at LEAST, and I mean very least, one group of 55+ to consistently pull and drop the mobs that hold the corroded for Thurgardin armor, and from all the guides I've read it's considered the easiest armor to complete. I've seen these mobs fought by a full group of 50's and I've watched the full group of 50's run like little children as fast as they could with the mobs on their tails. <br><br>I don't know what server you're from but I know on several there are guild alliances such as the XA where high level members of several small guilds band together to take out MOB's that couldn't be dropped by any guild individually. This seems to be a highly effective tactic and allows the guilds to keep their higher level members without fear of losing them to the larger guilds.<br><br>As for armor upgrades, there are some fine armors out there. Many are better than the gold/bronze you're wearing. Bronze has good ac but is a bit on the heavy side. The clerical quest armor is crap IMHO. It's got nice ac but the stat modifiers are a bit dissapointing.<br><br>Chakfor, The Dwarven Cleric of Brell<br>Reminding you that size really doesn't matter<br>&nbsp;<br>"You want proof of Brell's power? The proof is in the bottle, the higher the proof the better!"</td></tr>
