<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=98619895934350></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f98619895934350><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=7&mid=98619895934350>RE: A new Cleric...LF Advice..8)</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=7&mid=98619895934350#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=340><span id=Scholar>Chakfor</span></a>, <span id=Scholar>Scholar</span><br><span id=notbold>33 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Mon, Apr 2nd 4:09 AM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Excellent<span id=notbold>[4.50]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>As a dwarf pull all your points into wis and then put the spare 5 into str. Your strength is already high but it never hurts to have a bit more. You'll find the extra wisdom bonus allows you to sacrifice on +wisdom equipment and wear things with a higher AC which helps with the aggro. <br><br>As soon as you get dodge start taking hits. Do it on purpose. You want dodge maxxed out asap. <br><br>Always keep divine aura memmed, it's even more important than dodge. If I'm fairly close to a zone and the tanks are taking a beating, wizzies are oom, I'm oom, and we have to make a break for it. Just pop DA and tell the tanks to leave the mob on ya. Then bolt. You'll likely save a tank and have a friend for life.<br><br>Remember that if you're Full Mana there's no use for you to keep medding. I've been in groups with two clerics where one will be full and still sitting. You might not do much damage but it all adds up, at least you're taking care of the mobs natural regen :) And it's a wonderful time to work on those combat skills.<br><br>The xp in Lake of Ill omen plays out at level 30 so you got some very good advice there. I didn't hit Paw though. I went to the next zone, Frontier Mountains. My cleric is first character so I needed cash, I made enough there to completely cover a new set of armor and have some left over for a vacation to Velious. Overthere is a nice place as well but I happen to think that the cougars in Iceclad are MUCH better xp than OT..And once you hit 34 the Ulthorks in Eastern Wastes make OT look like a nerfed zone.<br><br>The most important thing to playing a cleric is this though....HAVE FUN!!!! You'll never lack for a group, you'll make a LOT of friends, you'll help a lot of people. But if you're not having fun it's really not worth it.<br>&nbsp;<br>"You want proof of Brell's power? The proof is in the bottle, the higher the proof the better!"</td></tr>
