	   <tr><td colspan=2>You go girl.&nbsp;&nbsp;=P<br><br>Some other things to point out;<br><br>/em clears his throat....<br>A lot of people out there don't know how to play their class, let alone another they've never even tried.  I once grouped with a ShadowKnight (We were all mid 20's in the group, at the Sarnak Fort in LOIO) who did not know what a Cleric was....<br>And this left me wondering...how did someone survive to their mid twenties and have NEVER heard of a Cleric?  It's all situational.  This was probably someone who went out, bought the game, and made an Iksar as his first character.  Nothing wrong with that, but he (Like me) had probably soloed his way up to there.  (I soloed until 21, when I started seriously grouping).  And having been born and raised in Cabilis, the only healer class he would have ever encountered was a Shaman, who many times at our level still try to melee.  Anyway, my point is this.<br>If you come across an uneducated person, try to teach them how you work.  If they don't know the full abilities of a Cleric, then they will get people killed.  Explain to them that you DON'T melee, that you sit on your butt to buff and heal people.<br>Also, I've sat groups down and explained to them how other classes play, too.  I had to halt the pulls from one group because our Chanter almost died; the Ranger was NOT assisting, and kept breaking mez.  So since out Enchanter wouldn't tell them what was up, (She was SOOOOO nice, to a fault.  =P)  I did.<br>I also, at lower levels, grouped with a monk who didn't know what mana was.../sigh<br>Anyway, I was the same myself.  I learned a lot from an Enchantress I grouped with in my low teens.  She had a high level Cleric alt, and taught me everything I know, even some stuff I can't do yet because they involve spells I don't have yet.  =P<br>I've been put in situations where I only had enough mana to cast one heal, but two people were dying...sometimes you have to let that happen...so you pick the more important group member.  Don't let your tank die to save someone who can't absorb damage anyway; you lose your tank you lose your group.  It's all a matter of situation.  In higher levels you'll be wanting to save the wizzie/druid, so they can evac out.  I've been told that in this case, you cast an area effect or group heal (This'll taunt most anything onto you), cast Divine Aura to go invincible, and be ready to click it off a few seconds before the wizzie/druid's port spell is complete.  (If you're invincible, then the port will not take you.  You don't want to be left behind.  =P)<br><br>Anyway, enough rambling from me...<br><br>Jarochai Alabaster<br>28th Dwarven Cleric of Brell Serelis<br>Proud member of Exile<br>Brell Serelis server<br><br>Anyone have any questions, pop into brell and /who me.  If I'm on, I'll try to get in some time to talk if I'm not in a fast group.  =)<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
