<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=9848485189325></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f9848485189325><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=7&mid=9848485189325>Where to hunt for Evil Clerics at 35 to 45</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=7&mid=9848485189325#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <span id= >Anonymous</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Sat, Mar 17th 12:01 PM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Default<span id=notbold>[2.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>When you hit 35 and want out of the "hell" level fast.&nbsp;&nbsp;Get a Necro and a warrior friend and head to the Druid ring in WC.  The three druids there, Ceel, Shadow and Sil are great xp and loot.  They have, on average, an 8 minute spawn time.  two of them give me half a blue of xp at 39 still.  The loot is pretty good too.  Fine Steel and some chain mail.  Ina 4 hour period I have gotten a bub and a half yellow and nearly 100 plat for my trouble.  The best thing to do is to fear one of the Druids and work on the other.  Keep an eye on the feared Druid while the Warrior and Necro take out the unfeared one.  Myself, a 35 Warrior and a 36 Rogue has done this.  But a Necro works best because of the DoTs take them down REAL fast.  Keep and eye of life totals while watching for the feared Druid.  This will take a few times to get it right, but once you work out the strategy and get things rolling, even a heal is few and far between when the three of you get on a roll.<br>Hope this helps my Dark Brethren, good luck and good hunting to you<br>Shanay Kenafin 1st Daughter of House Kenafin<br>(Brell)<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 >&nbsp;</td><td align=right valign=bottom>
